## Anti-patterns

- ❌ Filtering `_index/workbooks.csv` by table-name only. The CSV `table_full_name` includes a Synapse-style `schema.table` prefix; without a schema check, `accounts` matches both `bi_db.accounts` and `Customer.accounts`.
- ❌ Re-running the extractor inside the agent loop per object. Always batch all names into one `--tables-file` invocation.
- ❌ Writing per-object Tableau MDs into `knowledge/uc_domains/{domain}/`. The extractor already writes them under `knowledge/tableau/{DB}_{schema}/`; cross-link from the per-object wiki in P5 instead.
- ❌ Treating zero-hit objects as failure. Bronze ingest tables routinely have zero Tableau usage — the canonical view above them is the Tableau target.
